# Engineering Quality Rules

- Build modular components and isolate business logic from presentation.
- Reuse existing primitives before creating new abstractions.
- Keep components small and composable.
- After a meaningful set of changes: run build, typecheck, and tests.
- Prefer file-local clarity over over-abstraction.
